import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%m/%d/%Y', errors='coerce')
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month
    avg_temp = data.groupby('month')['temperature'].mean()
    plt.plot(avg_temp, marker='o', color='blue')
    plt.title('What is the average temperature distribution in Seattle throughout the year?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Month')
    plt.ylabel('Average Temperature')
    plt.xticks(range(1, 13))
    plt.ylim(40, 70)
    plt.axhline(avg_temp.max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Max: {avg_temp.max():.2f}')
    plt.axhline(avg_temp.min(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f'Min: {avg_temp.min():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%m/%d/%Y', errors='coerce')
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month
    monthly_precipitation = data.groupby('month')['precipitation'].sum()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(monthly_precipitation.index, monthly_precipitation.values)
    ax.set_xlabel('Month')
    ax.set_ylabel('Total Precipitation')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of precipitation in Seattle throughout the year?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['month'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%m/%d/%Y', errors='coerce').dt.month_name()
    data = data.groupby('month')['cloud_cover'].mean().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(data['month'], data['cloud_cover'], color='skyblue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Month')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average Cloud Cover')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of cloud cover in Seattle throughout the year?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
